**Rules of Uniform Usage**

1\. All uniforms must be approved or sold by the United States Armed Forces.  
2\. All ranks must follow the uniform guidelines.   
3\. Military Police have the right to arrest any individual who does not follow the proper guidelines with multiple warnings.  
4\. High Command has the right to punish or demote any individual that does not follow the guidelines despite multiple warnings.  
5\. Custom uniforms or USAF uniforms that are not sold or distributed by official USAF divisions/subdivisions are not allowed.  
6\. You must have a realistic skin tone at all times.  
7\. Any rank can be demoted/exiled if not following the uniform guidelines.  
8\. You can wear formal sunglasses.  
 9\. Officers can wear their divisional officer formals while attending United States Military Academy.  
10\. High Command can wear their divisional high command uniforms while attending the United States Military Academy.  
11\. Officers and High Command must be out of formals if attending a training at the academy.
